race.description: Hyundai Palisade Hybrid C,G&E Maiden Handicap
race.comment: SPONARS (3) is better than he showed here last start when getting well back in the run, though he did finish off nicely to be just 2.3L off the winner. He maps for a better run this time around with Costin replacing the apprentice hoop. Knocking on the door of a maiden win and this presents as a grand opportunity. EL TORO MACHO (1) has been solid in his two career efforts, finishign 1.5L off the winner as the favourite at Hawkesbury last time out. The blinkers go on now and while the draw is tricky, he has shown some early speed to begin his career. Expecting another bold effort today. BOTANIST (4) pulled up mildly lame first-up at Rosehill over 1400m and will find this a much easier assignment. He'll need some things to go his way from the draw, but he's shown class at the trials and he can improve sharply. VIVA MAURICIO (8) resumes a gelding and can return on a positive note.
